   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim">
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Type: element_component_classification_item 
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.element_component_classification_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Entity: element_component_classification_group  
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.element_component_classification_group"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim.element_component_classification_group">
An <b>element_component_classification_group</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="group_schema:ir_express:group_schema.group"/> for the classification of instances of the entities listed in the 
<express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.element_component_classification_item"/> type.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Entity: element_component_classification_group  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.element_component_classification_group.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim.element_component_classification_group.wr:WR1">
An <b>element_component_classification_group</b> shall be used as the <express_ref linkend="management_resources_schema:ir_express:management_resources_schema.classification_assignment.assigned_class"/> by at least
one <express_ref linkend="Classification_assignment:mim:Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment"/> instance.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Entity: negative_component  
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.negative_component"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim.negative_component">
A <b>negative_component</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> that represents a volume of space that is removed from
some shape.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Entity: negative_component  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.negative_component.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim.negative_component.wr:WR1">
A <b>negative_component</b> shall identify a shape element of a 
			<express_ref linkend="building_item:mim:Building_item_mim.building_element"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Entity: opening  
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.opening"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim.opening">
An <b>opening</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.negative_component"/> that represents a volume of space that passes through a
structural or enclosing element and serves a functional purpose.
The kind of opening is specified within a <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.element_component_classification_group"/> that is associated with the <b>opening</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Entity: opening  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.opening.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim.opening.wr:WR1">
An <b>opening</b> shall be referred to as items by one instance of <express_ref linkend="Classification_assignment:mim:Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment"/> that 
refers to an <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.element_component_classification_group"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Entity: positive_component  
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.positive_component"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim.positive_component">
A <b>positive_component</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> that represents a solid volume that is added to some shape.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Entity: positive_component  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.positive_component.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim.positive_component.wr:WR1">
A <b>positive_component</b> shall identify a shape element of a 
			<express_ref linkend="building_item:mim:Building_item_mim.building_element"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_component_mim  Entity: recess  
   <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.recess"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Building_component_mim.recess">
A <b>recess</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="building_component:mim:Building_component_mim.negative_component"/> that represents a volume of space that does not pass through a
structural or enclosing element.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>
